  "body": "Requires https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/issues/179\r\n\r\nRepresent items on the nodeStack and on the hashStack as special type of \"data carrying\" opcodes, for example `NODECONST <node>` and `HASHCONST <hash>`. Then express the actions of each opcode as a reduction rule of the form:\r\n````\r\nNODECONST[node] HASHCONST[hash] EXTENSION[key]   |=>\r\nNODECONST[shortNode{Key: key, Val: node}] HASHCONST [Keccak(rlp(compact(key)) | rlp(hash))]\r\n````\r\nThe rules like above can be applied to one instruction (there may be more instructions to the right), and the things that it pops from the stack are to the left of the opcode.\r\nInterestingly, in this model more than one reductions may happen simultaneously, but the order of the reductions does not matter for the end result.\r\n",
